The goal is to show that applying the functor map with different corec functions produces the same result. This should follow from the fact that the bisimulation relation ensures the destructions are related via `LiftR`, and we can use the QPF lifting lemma along with the fact that the two sides produce bisimilar coalgebras which map to the same quotient element.

